Scientific acceptance of Intelligent Design would require redefining science to allow [[supernatural]] explanations of observed phenomena, an approach its proponents describe as theistic realism or [[theistic science]].  It puts forth a number of arguments in support of the existence of a designer, the most prominent of which are [[irreducible complexity]] and [[specified complexity]].<ref name="discovery">

