Intelligent design was developed by a group of [[United States|American]] creationists who revised their argument in the [[creation<U+2013>evolution controversy]] to circumvent court rulings such as the [[United States Supreme Court]]'s ''[[Edwards v. Aguillard]]'' decision, which barred the teaching of "[[Creation Science]]" in public schools on the grounds of breaching the [[Separation of church and state in the United States|separation of church and state]].<ref name="kitz21">
